Package org.eclipse.rap.rwt.widgets

Interface Summary
BrowserCallback This callback interface is used to inform application code that the result of script execution or evaluation is available.
DialogCallback This callback interface is used to inform application code that a dialog was closed.
 

Class Summary
BrowserUtil Utility class to work with non-blocking browser script execution.
ClusteredSynchronizer Instances of this class provide synchronization support for displays in high-availability cluster environments.
DialogUtil Utility class to work with non-blocking dialogs.
ExternalBrowser Deprecated. Use UrlLauncher instead
FileUpload A button-like widget allowing to select a file from the client's file system and to upload this file to a given URL using HTTP POST.
